Regional cerebral blood flow measured by three-dimensional stereotactic surface projections (3D-SSP) of 123I-IMP SPECT in Parkinson disease patients with cognitive impairment. We investigated the regional cerebral blood flow (rCBF) in 8 patients with Parkinson disease (PD) with cognitive impairment (age 64-82 years, Mini-Mental State Examination score = MMSE score